1
00:00:02,202 --> 00:00:04,569
<i>THE DECEASED</i>                    
<i>IS NOT TO BE PICKED UP</i>          
<i>UNTIL THIS COMING SATURDAY?</i>     


2
00:00:04,638 --> 00:00:08,373
YES, JUST AFTER DAWN.           
UM, DETAILS FOR THE ARRANGEMENTS
ARE ALL THERE.                  


3
00:00:08,442 --> 00:00:11,643
        <i> AND A CHOICE OF CASKET</i> 
         <i> AND CEMETERY.</i>         


4
00:00:11,711 --> 00:00:14,979
            <i> I WOULD PREFER</i>     
            <i> A QUIET SERVICE.</i>   


5
00:00:15,048 --> 00:00:19,050
OF COURSE, MISS WILL.           
THE DECEASED WAS YOUR FATHER?   


6
00:00:19,119 --> 00:00:20,986
                <i> IS</i> MY FATHER.  


7
00:00:21,054 --> 00:00:23,555
IF YOUR FATHER                  
IS STILL ALIVE, THEN WHY--      


8
00:00:23,623 --> 00:00:27,058
        JUST HAVE A CASKET READY
        SATURDAY MORNING.       


9
00:00:27,127 --> 00:00:29,361
                PLEASE.         


10
00:01:01,028 --> 00:01:02,961
            [ Engine Starts ]   


11
00:01:19,980 --> 00:01:21,913
<i>[ Young Jarod ]</i>                 
<i>I DON'T WANNA DIE.</i>              


12
00:01:21,982 --> 00:01:24,415
        BUT I KNOW IT'S TOO LATE
        TO CHANGE ANY OF THAT.  


13
00:01:25,752 --> 00:01:27,719
[ Young Sydney ]                
THERE'S NOTHING                 
YOU WANNA CONFESS?              


14
00:01:29,089 --> 00:01:31,022
        [ Young Jarod ]         
        YOU KEEP ASKING ME      
        FOR THE TRUTH...        


15
00:01:31,091 --> 00:01:34,559
WHEN THAT'S ALL                 
I'VE EVER GIVEN YOU.            


16
00:01:34,628 --> 00:01:38,396
[ Young Sydney ]                
EVEN IN THE FACE OF DEATH,      
YOU MAINTAIN YOUR INNOCENCE.    


17
00:01:38,465 --> 00:01:40,766
                    YES.        


18
00:01:40,835 --> 00:01:43,702
        HE'S INNOCENT, SYDNEY.  


19
00:01:43,771 --> 00:01:47,071
                AN INNOCENT MAN 
                IS GOING TO DIE.


20
00:01:50,043 --> 00:01:52,577
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>OFF THE BUS! MOVE IT!</i>           
<i>MOVE IT! MOVE IT!</i>               


21
00:01:52,646 --> 00:01:54,947
<i>YOU HEARD THE MAN,</i>              
<i>SIDE BY SIDE!</i>                   


22
00:01:55,015 --> 00:02:00,419
<i>LINE UP AND SHUT UP!</i>            
<i>LET'S GO! MOVE IT!</i>              


23
00:02:05,559 --> 00:02:07,692
WELCOME TO OAKFIELD             
PENITENTIARY, GENTLEMEN.        


24
00:02:07,761 --> 00:02:10,629
    SOUND OFF.                  


25
00:02:10,698 --> 00:02:14,199
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


26
00:02:59,046 --> 00:03:02,613
<i>[ Sydney ] THERE'S BEEN</i>         
<i>A BREAKTHROUGH CONCERNING</i>       
<i>JAROD'S NEXT DESTINATION.</i>       


27
00:03:04,218 --> 00:03:08,387
"TOP HAT CAFÉ PAY PHONE.        
 JANUARY, WEEKEND OF THE 15th,  


28
00:03:08,455 --> 00:03:13,559
MEETING WITH COWBOY             
REGARDING PARKER BROTHERS."     


29
00:03:18,298 --> 00:03:20,565
I DON'T HAVE A BROTHER,         
DO I, SYDNEY?                   


30
00:03:20,634 --> 00:03:24,236
            THAT I DON'T KNOW.  


31
00:03:24,304 --> 00:03:27,038
    WHAT WE DO KNOW IS THE 15th 
    IS THIS COMING WEEKEND,     


32
00:03:27,107 --> 00:03:30,675
    AND THAT NOTE IS DISTINCTLY 
    WRITTEN IN JAROD'S HAND.    


33
00:03:30,743 --> 00:03:34,580
    - CLEANUP TEAM FIND THIS?   
    - IN JAROD'S LAST LAIR,     


34
00:03:34,648 --> 00:03:39,050
    STUCK IN THE TOILET PIPE    
    AFTER HAVING BEEN FLUSHED.  


35
00:03:41,422 --> 00:03:44,589
        OKAY, THE ARRANGEMENTS  
        ARE ALL SET, SYDNEY.    


36
00:03:44,658 --> 00:03:47,425
                <i> UH, OH, UH--</i>   


37
00:03:47,494 --> 00:03:50,195
GO ON, BROOTS.                  
WHAT ARRANGEMENTS?              


38
00:03:50,263 --> 00:03:52,196
            MR. BROOTS          
            WILL BE JOINING US. 


39
00:03:52,266 --> 00:03:55,233
<i>UH, THE DIRECTOR THINKS</i>         
<i>A LITTLE TECHNICAL SUPPORT</i>      
<i>MIGHT HELP.</i>                     


40
00:03:56,303 --> 00:03:58,670
<i>TECHNICAL SUPPORT?</i>              


41
00:03:58,738 --> 00:04:02,273
        <i> WELL, SHE THINKS</i>       
        <i> THAT SOME DETAILS</i>      
        <i> ARE GETTING OVERLOOKED,</i>


42
00:04:02,342 --> 00:04:07,579
THAT YOU AND SYDNEY ARE MAYBE   
A LITTLE TOO EMOTIONALLY        
INVOLVED WITH JAROD.            


43
00:04:07,648 --> 00:04:09,781
AND YOU'RE THE FIX?             


44
00:04:09,850 --> 00:04:11,783
                    WELL--      
                    [ Snickers ]


45
00:04:11,851 --> 00:04:13,952
<i>AN-- AN OBJECTIVE EYE, MAYBE.</i>   


46
00:04:14,021 --> 00:04:17,588
        UH, I'LL GET THE CAR.   


47
00:04:17,657 --> 00:04:20,458
♪♪ [ Whistling ]                


48
00:04:22,962 --> 00:04:25,363
            DULLER THAN HOCKEY  
            IN SEPTEMBER.       


49
00:04:25,432 --> 00:04:28,400
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>NEVER FORGET, MR. BRADLEY,</i>      
<i>THAT IN THIS PLACE,</i>             


50
00:04:28,468 --> 00:04:31,969
<i>WE ARE DEALING STRICTLY WITH</i>    
<i>A MENTALITY OF DESPERATION.</i>     


51
00:04:32,038 --> 00:04:35,607
        A DESPERATION BORN      
        FROM BEING LOCKED DOWN  
        IN A 10-BY-10 CELL...   


52
00:04:35,676 --> 00:04:38,976
            FOR 20, 30 YEARS,   
            SOMETIMES LONGER.   


53
00:04:39,045 --> 00:04:42,079
I WOULD SAY THAT DESPERATION    
WAS A GOOD WORD FOR THAT, SIR.  


54
00:04:42,148 --> 00:04:46,284
        A MAN'S FIBER, IF HE    
        HAD ANY TO BEGIN WITH,  
        QUICKLY FRAYS.          


55
00:04:46,353 --> 00:04:51,289
<i>IT'S YOUR JOB TO KEEP</i>           
<i>THOSE FRAYED ENDS KNOTTED.</i>      


56
00:04:51,358 --> 00:04:54,092
            YOU'RE HERE BECAUSE 
            OF YOUR EXPERIENCE  
            UNDER DURESS.       


57
00:04:54,161 --> 00:04:58,096
    WITH THE CARL WILL EXECUTION
    ON SATURDAY, THERE PROMISES 
    TO BE PLENTY OF THAT.       


58
00:04:58,165 --> 00:05:01,566
SOUNDS LIKE HE'S GOT            
ALL THE CLASSIC SYMPTOMS        
OF A CAREER CRIMINAL.           


59
00:05:03,137 --> 00:05:06,471
CARL WILL HAS A CRIMINAL RECORD 
DATING BACK 30 YEARS.           


60
00:05:06,539 --> 00:05:10,108
                CAR THEFT,      
                ARMED ROBBERY,  


61
00:05:10,177 --> 00:05:15,247
A DOZEN OTHER FELONY VIOLATIONS 
LEADING TO THE BRUTAL MURDER    
OF A FELLOW INMATE.             


62
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:19,317
    YOU WORKED FOLSOM           
    DURING THE '91 INMATE RIOT. 


63
00:05:19,386 --> 00:05:22,820
I'M PROUD TO SAY                
THAT WE SQUELCHED THAT ONE      
WITH EXTREME PREJUDICE.         


64
00:05:22,889 --> 00:05:25,357
    WE DON'T WIPE NOSES.        


65
00:05:25,425 --> 00:05:27,825
    WE DON'T LEND SHOULDERS     
    TO CRY ON.                  


66
00:05:27,895 --> 00:05:32,196
    WE MANAGE, MR. BRADLEY,     
    WITH, AS YOU SAY,           
    EXTREME PREJUDICE.          


67
00:05:32,265 --> 00:05:36,268
I'M SURE THE EXECUTION          
WILL SEND A MESSAGE             
TO THE ENTIRE POPULATION.       


68
00:05:36,336 --> 00:05:38,837
    THAT'S THE IDEA.            


69
00:05:43,677 --> 00:05:46,444
<i>HE'S NOT IN THERE,</i>              
<i>AND NONE OF THE LOCALS</i>          
<i>HAVE SEEN HIM.</i>                  


70
00:05:46,512 --> 00:05:49,347
                        MM-HMM. 
            [ Clears Throat ]   


71
00:05:49,416 --> 00:05:51,683
            MAYBE WE SHOULD     
            STAKE HIM OUT.      


72
00:05:51,752 --> 00:05:54,119
THEY DIDN'T LET YOU             
HAVE A WEAPON, DID THEY?        


73
00:05:54,187 --> 00:05:55,987
                    NO.         


74
00:05:58,425 --> 00:06:02,694
AND WHERE DO YOU PROPOSE        
WE DO OUR STAKEOUT?             


75
00:06:07,801 --> 00:06:10,368
                RIGHT THERE.    


76
00:06:13,140 --> 00:06:16,007
<i>[ Man ] SO, JAROD,</i>              
<i>HOW MANY MEN DID THEY RUN</i>       
<i>ON A SHIFT AT FOLSOM?</i>           


77
00:06:16,075 --> 00:06:19,678
OH, WE HAD A CREW               
OF 35 DURING THE WEEK,          
SLIGHTLY LESS ON THE WEEKENDS.  


78
00:06:19,746 --> 00:06:21,679
        I HEAR WARDEN HARPER'S  
        A TOUGH MAN.            


79
00:06:21,748 --> 00:06:24,348
HIS NAME IS HOPKINS.            


80
00:06:24,417 --> 00:06:27,318
                RIGHT, HOPKINS. 
    MORRIS.                     


81
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:30,722
            <i> AH, JAROD BRADLEY,</i> 
            <i> TOMMY LARSON.</i>      


82
00:06:30,791 --> 00:06:32,891
        BRADLEY.                
        THE GUY FROM FOLSOM?    


83
00:06:32,959 --> 00:06:35,593
        AND ALL POINTS WEST.    
                TOMMY CAN       
                SHOW YOU AROUND.


84
00:06:35,662 --> 00:06:41,166
        UH, KEEP BOTH EYES OPEN.
        THE ANIMALS             
        ARE GETTING RESTLESS.   


85
00:06:41,234 --> 00:06:44,936
LET ME TAKE YOU OUT,            
SHOW YOU THE MAIN YARD.         


86
00:06:45,005 --> 00:06:48,707
<i>MOST OF THE POPULATION</i>          
<i>SPENDS FOUR OR FIVE HOURS</i>       
<i>A DAY HERE.</i>                     


87
00:06:48,776 --> 00:06:52,410
    DIFFERENT ZOO,              
    SAME ROUTINE.               


88
00:06:52,479 --> 00:06:55,380
GOTTA MAKE SURE                 
THEY DON'T KILL EACH OTHER      
AND HERD 'EM IN AT THE BELL.    


89
00:06:55,449 --> 00:06:57,715
                SEEMS TENSE.    


90
00:06:57,784 --> 00:07:01,987
YEAH, WELL, IT'LL EASE UP       
AFTER THE, UH, THE EVENT.       


91
00:07:02,055 --> 00:07:05,256
                    THE EVENT?  
        EXECUTION.              


92
00:07:05,325 --> 00:07:07,392
YOU GET IT UP CLOSE             
AND PERSONAL.                   


93
00:07:07,461 --> 00:07:09,894
    NEW GUY GETS DEATH WATCH.   


94
00:07:11,565 --> 00:07:13,698
                    WHY ME?     
<i>I DON'T KNOW</i>                    
<i>HOW IT WAS AT FOLSOM,</i>           


95
00:07:13,766 --> 00:07:18,803
BUT AROUND HERE,                
IT'S CONSIDERED BAD LUCK TO GET 
TOO CLOSE TO A CONDEMNED MAN.   


96
00:07:18,872 --> 00:07:20,805
    THEY MAKE THE NEW GUY DO IT.


97
00:07:20,873 --> 00:07:22,974
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>WALKIN' THROUGH.</i>                


98
00:07:29,215 --> 00:07:31,649
            IS THAT HIM?        


99
00:07:32,852 --> 00:07:35,052
<i>[ Buzzer Buzzes ]</i>               


100
00:07:39,025 --> 00:07:42,394
            - LARSON.           
            - WHAT?             


101
00:07:42,462 --> 00:07:45,129
        IS THAT THE MAN         
        THEY'RE GOING TO KILL?  


102
00:07:52,339 --> 00:07:54,271
        YEAH, THAT'S HIM.       


103
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:03,315
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>WHAT DO YOU MEAN</i>                
<i>YOU'RE BOOKED UP?</i>               


104
00:08:03,383 --> 00:08:05,650
    WHO THE HELL WOULD          
    PURPOSELY STAY...           


105
00:08:05,719 --> 00:08:08,720
        AT THE PARK PLACE MOTEL?


106
00:08:08,788 --> 00:08:12,523
WELL, WE GOT A CONVENTION.      
THE ELECTRIC COMPANY            
BOOKED THE ENTIRE FACILITY.     


107
00:08:12,592 --> 00:08:14,960
        DO YOU KNOW THIS MAN?   
JAROD.                          


108
00:08:15,028 --> 00:08:16,961
YEAH, HE COMES THROUGH HERE     
EVERY NOW AND THEN.             


109
00:08:17,030 --> 00:08:19,330
MATTER OF FACT, HE SAID         
SOMETHING ABOUT PASSING THROUGH 
THIS WEEKEND.                   


110
00:08:19,399 --> 00:08:21,632
GOT A MEETING OR SOMETHING.     
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.             


111
00:08:21,701 --> 00:08:26,471
YOU BEING FRIENDS OF HIS        
AND ALL, YOU AND YOUR BROTHER   
AND-- AND YOUR DAD,             


112
00:08:26,539 --> 00:08:30,174
YOU CAN STAY                    
IN THE CELEBRITY ROOM THAT      
I KEEP OPEN FOR SPECIAL GUESTS. 


113
00:08:30,243 --> 00:08:32,210
    CELEBRITY ROOM.             


114
00:08:32,279 --> 00:08:36,047
BURL IVES STAYED HERE ONCE.     
WE EVEN HAD MAMA CASS.          


115
00:08:36,116 --> 00:08:38,049
        NOT TO MENTION          
        THAT OSMOND BOY.        


116
00:08:38,118 --> 00:08:41,386
    YOU KNOW,                   
    THE GOOFY-LOOKING ONE       
    WITH THE-- THE BIG EARS.    


117
00:08:42,789 --> 00:08:45,890
                YOU KNOW, I BET 
                IT WASN'T DONNY.


118
00:08:47,460 --> 00:08:50,628
            MAIL CALL           
            FOR INMATE COCKRAN. 


119
00:08:54,801 --> 00:08:57,135
                        THANKS. 


120
00:09:00,106 --> 00:09:05,143
OH, I'M SORRY.                  
I WASN'T WATCHING               
WHERE I WAS GOING.              


121
00:09:05,212 --> 00:09:07,145
YOU OKAY, BOSS?                 


122
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:11,049
        I'M FINE.               
        AND THE NAME IS JAROD,  
        MR.--                   


123
00:09:11,117 --> 00:09:13,718
    COCKRAN, HENRY.             


124
00:09:13,787 --> 00:09:15,753
            WELL, IT'S NICE     
            TO MEET YOU, HENRY. 


125
00:09:15,822 --> 00:09:18,022
<i>[ Buzzer Buzzes ]</i>               


126
00:09:23,997 --> 00:09:27,098
YOU'RE NEW AROUND HERE.         
                    YES, I AM.  


127
00:09:27,167 --> 00:09:32,003
                        AND YOU?
OH, I'VE BEEN WALKING           
THESE HALLS FOR 27 YEARS.       


128
00:09:32,072 --> 00:09:34,538
            <i> THAT'S A LONG TIME.</i>


129
00:09:34,608 --> 00:09:37,675
THERE ISN'T A COCKROACH         
I'M NOT ON A FIRST NAME         
BASIS WITH.                     


130
00:09:37,744 --> 00:09:40,711
        IS THAT MAIL FROM HOME? 
UH, MY WIFE.                    


131
00:09:40,780 --> 00:09:44,082
SHE WRITES ME EVERY WEEK        
LIKE CLOCKWORK.                 


132
00:09:44,151 --> 00:09:47,685
SENDS ME SEEDS                  
FOR MY GARDEN.                  


133
00:09:47,754 --> 00:09:49,687
THESE SHOULD BE MARIGOLDS.      


134
00:09:49,756 --> 00:09:51,956
            <i> COCKRAN.</i>           


135
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:56,861
        <i> YOU GOT SOMEWHERE</i>      
        <i> TO BE, OLD-TIMER?</i>      


136
00:09:56,930 --> 00:09:59,097
    KITCHEN, BOSS.              


137
00:10:02,269 --> 00:10:04,936
THAT WHAT THEY CALL             
EXTREME PREJUDICE AT FOLSOM?    


138
00:10:05,005 --> 00:10:08,740
                YOU HAVE TO KNOW
                YOUR ENEMY.     


139
00:10:11,511 --> 00:10:13,944
        [ Male Reporter ]       
        TONIGHT WE BRING YOU    
        A STORY OF LOVE, LAW... 


140
00:10:14,014 --> 00:10:16,314
    <i> AND ITS CONNECTION BETWEEN</i> 
    <i> A MAN ON DEATH ROW...</i>      


141
00:10:16,383 --> 00:10:18,816
<i>AND A DAUGHTER WHOSE LIFE</i>       
<i>HAS BEEN A FIGHT TO FREE HIM.</i>   


142
00:10:18,885 --> 00:10:22,420
    TEN YEARS AGO, CARL WILL,   
    A CAREER CRIMINAL,          


143
00:10:22,488 --> 00:10:24,589
    <i> WAS SENTENCED TO FIVE YEARS</i>
    <i> FOR CAR THEFT.</i>             


144
00:10:24,657 --> 00:10:28,459
<i>ONLY WEEKS AWAY FROM PAROLE,</i>    
<i>HE WAS INVOLVED</i>                 
<i>IN A BLOODY ALTERCATION...</i>      


145
00:10:28,528 --> 00:10:32,397
INSIDE OAKFIELD PENITENTIARY,   
IN WHICH INMATE ANTHONY LEWIS   
WAS STABBED TO DEATH.           


146
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:35,667
<i>AFTER A SPEEDY TRIAL CONDUCTED</i>  
<i>BY THEN STATE ATTORNEY...</i>       


147
00:10:35,735 --> 00:10:37,802
        <i> AND PRESENT GOVERNOR</i>   
        <i> CHARLES EDWARDS,</i>       


148
00:10:37,870 --> 00:10:40,271
<i>WILL WAS CONVICTED</i>              
<i>OF FIRST-DEGREE MURDER...</i>       


149
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:42,574
<i>AND SENTENCED TO DIE</i>            
<i>IN THE GAS CHAMBER,</i>             


150
00:10:42,642 --> 00:10:46,043
<i>WHICH IS WHERE THE STORY</i>        
<i>TAKES A MOST UNUSUAL TURN.</i>      


151
00:10:46,112 --> 00:10:50,414
<i>AT THE TIME OF WILL'S INITIAL</i>   
<i>ARREST, HIS DAUGHTER JESSICA</i>    
<i>WAS A SENIOR IN HIGH SCHOOL.</i>    


152
00:10:50,484 --> 00:10:52,817
<i>JESSICA'S BELIEF IN HER FATHER</i>  
<i>FUELED HER TO SPEND</i>             
<i>THE NEXT SEVEN YEARS...</i>         


153
00:10:52,886 --> 00:10:58,022
<i>IN COLLEGE AND LAW SCHOOL,</i>      
<i>AND EVERY DAY SINCE,</i>            
<i>FIGHTING TO FREE HER FATHER.</i>    


154
00:10:58,091 --> 00:11:00,625
<i>BUT WITH THE GOVERNOR'S DENYING</i> 
<i>FINAL APPEAL...</i>                 


155
00:11:00,693 --> 00:11:03,128
<i>AND THE EXECUTION SCHEDULED</i>     
<i>FOR MIDNIGHT FRIDAY,</i>            


156
00:11:03,196 --> 00:11:07,165
<i>HER ODYSSEY OF LAW AND LOVE</i>     
<i>APPEARS TO BE AT AN END.</i>        


157
00:11:07,234 --> 00:11:09,667
<i>[ Jessica's Voice ]</i>             
<i>I LOVE MY FATHER,</i>               
<i>I BELIEVE IN HIM,</i>               


158
00:11:09,736 --> 00:11:11,802
<i>AND I WILL NEVER STOP FIGHTING.</i> 


159
00:11:21,447 --> 00:11:24,448
HOW DO YOU RESPOND              
TO JESSICA WILL'S CALL          
FOR CLEMENCY FROM THE GOVERNOR? 


160
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:27,084
    THE GOVERNOR'S REFUSAL      
    IS THE ONLY ANSWER I NEED.  


161
00:11:27,153 --> 00:11:29,153
    MISS WILL CALLS             
    THE QUICK PROCESSING        
    OF HER FATHER...            


162
00:11:29,222 --> 00:11:32,990
A POLITICAL ACT BY GOVERNOR     
EDWARDS BASED ON HIS REELECTION 
LAW AND ORDER PLATFORM.         


163
00:11:33,059 --> 00:11:37,295
- HOW DO YOU ANSWER THAT?       
- NO ONE DOUBTS MISS WILL'S LOVE
  OR DEVOTION TO HER FATHER,    


164
00:11:37,363 --> 00:11:39,964
BUT SHE IS WORKING FROM EMOTION,
AND WE'RE WORKING FROM FACT.    


165
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:42,333
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>WARDEN, WHAT FACTS ARE THOSE?</i>   


166
00:11:42,402 --> 00:11:47,138
    OFFICERS CLANCY AND LARSON  
    FOUND CARL WILL NEXT TO     
    THE BODY OF ANTHONY LEWIS,  


167
00:11:47,207 --> 00:11:49,874
            HOLDING             
            THE MURDER WEAPON.  


168
00:11:49,943 --> 00:11:53,377
    UNFORTUNATE AS IT IS,       
    WHEN YOU CONCENTRATE        
    TRANSGRESSORS IN THE SYSTEM,


169
00:11:53,446 --> 00:11:57,081
    THESE THINGS HAPPEN,        
    BUT THEY WON'T BE TOLERATED 
    BY ME OR THE GOVERNOR.      


170
00:11:57,150 --> 00:12:01,886
THE TIME HAS COME FOR US        
TO DO OUR JOB, AND WE'RE GOING  
TO DO IT AT DAWN SATURDAY.      


171
00:12:01,955 --> 00:12:05,422
    - THANK YOU.                
    - [ Reporters Clamoring ]   


172
00:12:08,394 --> 00:12:10,327
<i>[ Buzzer Buzzing ]</i>              


173
00:12:23,075 --> 00:12:26,210
    <i> DIDN'T YOU HEAR</i>            
    <i> IT'S BAD LUCK</i>              
    <i> BEING AROUND A DEAD MAN?</i>   


174
00:12:26,279 --> 00:12:28,913
    WELL, I'M THE NEW GUY.      


175
00:12:28,982 --> 00:12:32,150
    I HAVE NO CHOICE.           


176
00:12:32,218 --> 00:12:34,451
    <i> BON APPÉTIT.</i>               
                <i> I'M NOT HUNGRY.</i>


177
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:37,322
IT'S GRILLED PORTERHOUSE STEAK, 
MEDIUM RARE.                    


178
00:12:37,390 --> 00:12:40,057
    POACHED SNAP BEANS.         


179
00:12:41,794 --> 00:12:44,028
        THAT'S WHAT I ORDERED   
        FOR MY LAST MEAL.       


180
00:12:44,097 --> 00:12:46,197
        I KNOW.                 


181
00:12:46,266 --> 00:12:49,233
    THAT WASN'T SUPPOSED TO BE  
    FOR, UH, TWO DAYS.          


182
00:12:49,302 --> 00:12:52,570
WELL, IT'S YOUR FAVORITE.       
I FIGURED WHY WAIT.             


183
00:12:54,874 --> 00:12:57,508
THEY MOVE IN ON YOU,            
DON'T THEY?                     


184
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:02,212
THE WALLS.                      


185
00:13:02,281 --> 00:13:05,850
YOU STARE AT THEM LONG ENOUGH,  
AND YOU SWEAR THEY START        
CREEPING IN ON YOU.             


186
00:13:07,253 --> 00:13:10,521
YOU SOUND LIKE A MAN THAT'S     
BEEN ON THIS SIDE OF THE BARS.  


187
00:13:10,589 --> 00:13:12,523
IT'S TOUGH...                   


188
00:13:12,592 --> 00:13:14,559
    WHEN YOU DON'T              
    BELONG THERE.               


189
00:13:16,629 --> 00:13:19,097
    YOU'RE INNOCENT,            


190
00:13:19,165 --> 00:13:21,332
AT LEAST THAT'S WHAT            
YOU KEEP SAYING.                


191
00:13:21,401 --> 00:13:23,667
            NOBODY'S LISTENING. 


192
00:13:23,736 --> 00:13:25,803
        I AM.                   


193
00:13:25,872 --> 00:13:30,975
        YOU'RE TELLING ME A MAN 
        WEARING THAT UNIFORM    
        HASN'T HEARD THIS STORY?


194
00:13:31,044 --> 00:13:35,113
I'VE HEARD THE STORY.           
I'M INTERESTED IN THE TRUTH.    


195
00:13:39,118 --> 00:13:44,121
            I WAS HEADED BACK   
            TO BLOCK "C"        
            FROM LAUNDRY DETAIL.


196
00:13:44,190 --> 00:13:46,757
                I HEARD VOICES. 


197
00:13:46,826 --> 00:13:50,761
        SOME PEOPLE STRUGGLING  
        DOWN THE GANTRY.        


198
00:13:50,830 --> 00:13:53,764
        TURNED AROUND TO SEE    
        WHAT THE COMMOTION WAS. 


199
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:58,035
    GOT KNOCKED OUT.            
    WOKE UP IN THIS NIGHTMARE.  


200
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:03,107
        CORN BREAD OR FRITTERS? 


201
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:06,744
FRITTERS.                       
JUST LIKE YOU ASKED.            


202
00:14:06,813 --> 00:14:08,746
                JUST THE WAY    
                JESSICA ASKED.  


203
00:14:09,816 --> 00:14:11,749
        SHE ARRANGED ALL THIS.  


204
00:14:11,818 --> 00:14:13,818
SHE LOVES YOU VERY MUCH.        


205
00:14:13,886 --> 00:14:16,320
                    BRADLEY.    


206
00:14:16,389 --> 00:14:19,223
            THE PRISONER'S MEAL 
            IS DELIVERED.       


207
00:14:34,140 --> 00:14:38,175
    <i> [ Over Listening Device ]</i>  
    <i> OH, DARLIN',</i>               
    <i> I MISS YOU SO DAMN BAD.</i>    


208
00:14:38,244 --> 00:14:41,679
<i>I ACHE ALL OVER THINKING</i>        
<i>HOW PRETTY YOU LOOKED</i>           
<i>LAYING IN THAT BATHTUB.</i>         


209
00:14:41,748 --> 00:14:46,117
        <i> THAT MR. BUBBLE</i>        
        <i> DANCING ON YOUR SKIN</i>   
        <i> LIKE A LOVE POTION.</i>    


210
00:14:46,185 --> 00:14:49,353
<i>AND YOU STOOD UP</i>                
<i>AND I DRANK IN THE VISION</i>       
<i>OF YOUR PERFECTLY SHAPED--</i>      


211
00:14:49,422 --> 00:14:52,189
<i>[ Turns Off Device ]</i>            


212
00:14:52,258 --> 00:14:55,526
            [ Clears Throat ]   
            PHONE TAP SEEMS     
            TO BE WORKING.      


213
00:14:56,829 --> 00:15:00,664
    I GUESS I'LL POKE AROUND    
    THE ROOM FOR SIGNS OF JAROD.


214
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:03,768
        I'M GOING TO GO         
        OUT OF MY MIND.         


215
00:15:11,177 --> 00:15:13,110
        <i> "RELATIVE THINKING."</i>   


216
00:15:13,179 --> 00:15:16,313
            <i> "THE INNER MIND."</i>  


217
00:15:16,382 --> 00:15:20,585
        MY GOD! SYDNEY, IS JAROD
        ALL YOU THINK ABOUT?    


218
00:15:20,654 --> 00:15:23,187
            BECAUSE YOU DON'T?  


219
00:15:23,257 --> 00:15:26,891
    - THERE IS A LOT MORE       
      TO LIFE THAN JAROD.       
    - SUCH AS?                  


220
00:15:26,960 --> 00:15:30,361
        SUCH AS FUN.            
         SUCH AS SEX.           


221
00:15:30,430 --> 00:15:34,999
INTERESTING THAT                
IN A CONVERSATION               
ABOUT JAROD, YOU MENTION SEX.   


222
00:15:36,770 --> 00:15:40,471
                WELL, NOTHING   
                IN THE TOILET.  


223
00:15:44,277 --> 00:15:48,346
        HOW LONG HAS IT BEEN    
        SINCE YOU'VE BEEN       
        WITH A WOMAN, SYDNEY?   


224
00:15:48,415 --> 00:15:53,651
<i>SYDNEY'S PRIVATE LIFE</i>           
<i>IS NOT A SUBJECT</i>                
<i>FOR PUBLIC DISCUSSION.</i>          


225
00:15:53,719 --> 00:15:59,290
WELL, IT'S NOT HEALTHY,         
YOU KNOW, KEEPING ALL OF        
THAT ANIMAL EMOTION BOTTLED UP. 


226
00:15:59,359 --> 00:16:01,926
    NEXT THING YOU KNOW,        
    YOU'LL BE ON THE ROOF       
    WITH A RIFLE IN YOUR HANDS. 


227
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:08,432
YOU KNOW, I'VE BEEN             
SEEING A WOMAN.                 


228
00:16:10,003 --> 00:16:13,237
                REALLY. BROOTS. 


229
00:16:14,308 --> 00:16:16,341
            TELL US ABOUT HER.  


230
00:16:16,409 --> 00:16:18,743
        THERE'S NOT MUCH        
        TO TELL REALLY.         
        WE-- WE MET ONLINE.     


231
00:16:18,811 --> 00:16:21,012
            YOU PICK UP WOMEN   
            ON THE COMPUTER?    


232
00:16:22,315 --> 00:16:26,250
                HOW ROMANTIC.   
                DETAILS.        


233
00:16:28,154 --> 00:16:30,989
    <i> WELL, UH,</i>                  
    <i> SHE'S AN ACCOUNTANT.</i>       


234
00:16:31,058 --> 00:16:34,759
        SHE HAS THREE DOGS      
        AND A BIRD.             


235
00:16:34,828 --> 00:16:37,929
AND, UH, OH!                    
AND SHE'S A HUGE JOHN TESH FAN. 


236
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:41,532
            SOUNDS LIKE         
            A REAL WILDCAT.     


237
00:16:41,601 --> 00:16:44,970
        WHAT'S SHE LOOK LIKE?   


238
00:16:47,106 --> 00:16:50,808
YOU KNOW, I THINK, UH, I SHOULD 
START DUSTING FOR PRINTS.       


239
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:59,584
WE HAVEN'T                      
ACTUALLY MET... YET.            


240
00:17:03,590 --> 00:17:06,157
        YOU ARE PATHETIC.       


241
00:17:08,261 --> 00:17:11,963
        GOD, CAN THEY MAKE IT   
        ANY HOTTER IN HERE?     


242
00:17:18,137 --> 00:17:20,171
    <i> [ Miss Parker Groaning ]</i>   


243
00:17:21,474 --> 00:17:23,608
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>YOU ALL RIGHT, MISS PARKER?</i>     
        I'M OKAY.               


244
00:17:23,676 --> 00:17:27,311
    IT'S THIS, UH, SWILL        
    FROM THAT GREASY SPOON.     


245
00:17:28,482 --> 00:17:30,815
    <i> HOW MUCH MORE EXCITING</i>     
    <i> CAN THIS GET?</i>              


246
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:36,421
            LOOK, MONOPOLY.     


247
00:17:42,362 --> 00:17:44,795
<i>♪♪ [ Country ]</i>                  


248
00:17:46,432 --> 00:17:49,133
PSST. PSST.                     


249
00:17:52,772 --> 00:17:56,841
<i>YEAH, IT'S AMAZING</i>              
<i>WHAT THEY LET SIT DOWN</i>          
<i>IN THIS PLACE.</i>                  


250
00:17:58,177 --> 00:18:02,280
<i>MM, YOU SMELL SOMETHING?</i>        


251
00:18:02,348 --> 00:18:04,816
    [ Sniffing ]                


252
00:18:04,884 --> 00:18:07,218
SMELLS LIKE SOMEBODY'S          
ABOUT TO FRY.                   


253
00:18:07,286 --> 00:18:10,989
                WOULD YOU JUST  
                LEAVE ME ALONE? 
                PLEASE.         


254
00:18:11,058 --> 00:18:16,494
WHAT YOU GONNA DO               
IF I DON'T? HUH?                
<i>[ Door Bells Ring ]</i>             


255
00:18:17,931 --> 00:18:20,030
PULL OUT ONE OF THEM KNIVES     
LIKE YOUR DADDY DID?            


256
00:18:20,099 --> 00:18:22,567
<i>STICK ME WITH IT?</i>               


257
00:18:22,635 --> 00:18:26,170
    <i> JESSICA. HI, HONEY.</i>        
    <i> SORRY I'M LATE.</i>            


258
00:18:26,239 --> 00:18:29,874
    <i> TRAFFIC WAS A BEAR.</i>        


259
00:18:29,943 --> 00:18:33,878
    YOU WILL EXCUSE US,         
    WON'T YOU, GENTLEMEN?       


260
00:18:45,859 --> 00:18:49,727
    - THANK YOU.                
    - BET THAT'S HAPPENING      
      A LOT THESE DAYS.         


261
00:18:49,796 --> 00:18:52,663
            YOU HAVE NO IDEA.   


262
00:18:52,732 --> 00:18:55,699
    YOU'RE A GUARD              
    FROM THE PRISON.            


263
00:18:55,768 --> 00:18:59,104
    I'M OFF DUTY.               
        IT'S NOTHING PERSONAL,  


264
00:18:59,172 --> 00:19:04,742
        BUT IT'S JUST GUARDS    
        AREN'T HIGH ON MY LIST  
        OF DINNER COMPANIONS.   


265
00:19:04,811 --> 00:19:07,278
I JUST SHARED A MEAL            
WITH YOUR FATHER.               


266
00:19:09,082 --> 00:19:11,015
HE MISSES YOU VERY MUCH.        


267
00:19:15,588 --> 00:19:17,521
            WHY ARE YOU HERE?   


268
00:19:17,590 --> 00:19:20,792
        FATE.                   


269
00:19:20,860 --> 00:19:23,560
AND I DON'T THINK               
YOUR FATHER DESERVES HIS.       


270
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:30,868
        MY MOTHER LEFT          
        WHEN I WAS LITTLE,      
        BUT HE NEVER LEFT ME.   


271
00:19:30,937 --> 00:19:35,239
    WE LIVED IN                 
    THIS RUSTED-OUT AIRSTREAM   
    FOR MOST OF MY LIFE.        


272
00:19:35,308 --> 00:19:37,574
            YOU KNOW,           
            WE DIDN'T HAVE MUCH,


273
00:19:37,643 --> 00:19:39,977
        BUT HE ALWAYS MADE SURE 
        I HAD WHAT I NEEDED.    


274
00:19:42,315 --> 00:19:45,216
        LOOK, I'M NOT SAYING    
        THAT MY FATHER IS       
        THE EPITOME OF VIRTUE.  


275
00:19:45,285 --> 00:19:47,885
            I MEAN, HE WAS--    
            HE WAS PRETTY WILD  
            WHEN HE WAS YOUNGER.


276
00:19:47,954 --> 00:19:52,957
        BUT STEALING CARS       
        AND COMMITTING MURDER...


277
00:19:53,025 --> 00:19:55,359
            ARE WORLDS APART.   


278
00:19:58,297 --> 00:20:00,965
        HE SPENT FIVE YEARS     
        IN THAT LOCKUP.         


279
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:02,967
            HE WAS A WEEK AWAY  
            FROM PAROLE.        


280
00:20:03,036 --> 00:20:05,770
                HE HAD A JOB    
                ON THE OUTSIDE, 


281
00:20:05,839 --> 00:20:08,105
                AND I WAS       
                ON THE OUTSIDE. 


282
00:20:10,877 --> 00:20:13,277
                HE WOULDN'T HAVE
                DONE THAT TO ME.


283
00:20:20,753 --> 00:20:23,187
        DID YOU KNOW MONOPOLY   
        WAS DEVELOPED BY        
        CHARLES DARROW,         


284
00:20:23,256 --> 00:20:27,125
AN UNEMPLOYED HEATING ENGINEER  
FROM GERMANTOWN, PENNSYLVANIA   
IN 1935?                        


285
00:20:27,193 --> 00:20:29,260
YEAH, THAT'S FASCINATING.       


286
00:20:29,329 --> 00:20:32,830
        THE GAME WAS ORIGINALLY 
        REJECTED FOR CONTAINING 
        52 FUNDAMENTAL ERRORS,  


287
00:20:32,898 --> 00:20:36,333
<i>BUT THERE STILL HAVE BEEN</i>       
<i>OVER 100 MILLION SETS</i>           
<i>SOLD WORLDWIDE.</i>                 


288
00:20:36,403 --> 00:20:39,170
    YOU SOUND LIKE              
    QUITE AN EXPERT             
    ON THE SUBJECT.             


289
00:20:39,239 --> 00:20:41,639
            MONOPOLY CLUB,      
            HIGH SCHOOL.        


290
00:20:41,708 --> 00:20:45,543
        WHAT A SURPRISE.        
        [ Groans ]              


291
00:20:45,612 --> 00:20:48,880
                MISS PARKER,    
                YOU ALL RIGHT?  


292
00:20:48,948 --> 00:20:52,049
        IT'S JUST SO DAMN HOT   
        IN HERE.                


293
00:20:54,287 --> 00:20:58,722
<i>YOU KNOW-- [ Clears Throat ]</i>    
<i>THERE'S SOMETHING WRONG</i>         
<i>WITH THIS GAME.</i>                 


294
00:20:58,791 --> 00:21:02,693
    [ Grunts ]                  
    THERE'S SOMETHING WRONG     
    WITH THIS WHOLE DAMN THING. 


295
00:21:02,762 --> 00:21:06,164
<i>NO, THERE'S, UH--</i>               
<i>[ Clears Throat ]</i>               
<i>THERE'S SOMETHING MISSING HERE.</i> 


296
00:21:06,232 --> 00:21:09,967
    [ Grunts ]                  
    THE ONLY THING MISSING      
    IS JAROD.                   


297
00:21:12,539 --> 00:21:14,471
        - [ Groans ]            
        - MISS PARKER!          


298
00:21:14,540 --> 00:21:16,507
            <i> GET A DOCTOR NOW!</i>  


299
00:21:19,111 --> 00:21:21,345
        [ Computer Beeps ]      


300
00:21:27,053 --> 00:21:28,852
[ Beeps ]                       


301
00:21:33,326 --> 00:21:35,259
[ Beeps ]                       


302
00:21:37,330 --> 00:21:39,864
<i>[ Beeps ]</i>                       


303
00:21:54,347 --> 00:21:56,580
[ Inmates Chattering ]          


304
00:22:13,199 --> 00:22:15,132
                    NARCISSUS.  


305
00:22:15,201 --> 00:22:19,036
I CALL THEM DAFFODILS.          
THEY'RE MY WIFE'S FAVORITE.     


306
00:22:19,105 --> 00:22:21,806
            WELL, I CAN SEE WHY.
            THEY'RE BEAUTIFUL.  


307
00:22:21,874 --> 00:22:25,109
<i>TALK LIKE THAT,</i>                 
<i>AND NO ONE WILL BELIEVE</i>         
<i>YOU'RE REALLY A BULL.</i>           


308
00:22:25,178 --> 00:22:29,547
<i>ONLY THING THE OTHER GUARDS</i>     
<i>KNOW HOW TO GROW IS RESENTMENT.</i> 


309
00:22:29,616 --> 00:22:32,150
            <i> [ Man ]</i>            
            <i> WALKIN' THROUGH.</i>   


310
00:22:35,788 --> 00:22:38,589
        IS IT ALWAYS            
        THIS TENSE AROUND HERE  
        BEFORE AN EXECUTION?    


311
00:22:41,194 --> 00:22:43,861
    ALWAYS.                     


312
00:22:43,930 --> 00:22:46,330
                DID YOU KNOW    
                ANTHONY LEWIS?  


313
00:22:46,399 --> 00:22:49,800
NO. HE'D ONLY BEEN HERE         
A COUPLE OF DAYS.               


314
00:22:49,869 --> 00:22:52,469
    COUPLE OF DAYS?             
    HARDLY SEEMS LONG ENOUGH... 


315
00:22:52,538 --> 00:22:55,172
        FOR CARL WILL TO GROW   
        TO HATE HIM ENOUGH      
        TO WANNA KILL HIM.      


316
00:22:56,308 --> 00:22:59,310
    STRANGE THINGS              
    HAPPEN IN STIR.             


317
00:22:59,379 --> 00:23:02,146
        LIKE THE OTHER INMATES  
        WHO HAVE DIED IN HERE?  


318
00:23:03,282 --> 00:23:06,217
            <i> SEVEN IN THE LAST</i>  
            <i> FIVE YEARS.</i>        


319
00:23:06,285 --> 00:23:08,319
                <i> ALL ACCIDENTS?</i> 


320
00:23:08,387 --> 00:23:11,122
    <i> IT'S A LOT MORE</i>            
    <i> THAN THE NATIONAL AVERAGE.</i> 


321
00:23:11,191 --> 00:23:13,190
    I WOULDN'T KNOW ANYTHING    
    ABOUT THAT.                 


322
00:23:13,259 --> 00:23:18,662
OH, COME ON, HENRY,             
YOU'RE ON A FIRST NAME BASIS    
WITH THE ROACHES AROUND HERE.   


323
00:23:18,731 --> 00:23:20,931
        WHAT HAPPENED           
        WITH ANTHONY LEWIS...   


324
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:24,468
                AND THE OTHER   
                DEAD INMATES?   


325
00:23:26,605 --> 00:23:30,374
PRISON'S A PLACE                
TO KEEP YOUR HEAD DOWN          
AND YOUR MOUTH SHUT.            


326
00:23:30,443 --> 00:23:33,344
ESPECIALLY THIS PLACE.          


327
00:23:33,413 --> 00:23:36,414
    AND THIS WARDEN.            


328
00:23:36,482 --> 00:23:41,018
<i>[ Whistle Blows ]</i>               
<i>LET'S MOVE IT IN.</i>               


329
00:23:53,666 --> 00:23:56,800
        <i> [ Young Jarod ]</i>        
        <i> I HAVE TWO MINUTES</i>     
        <i> LEFT TO LIVE.</i>          


330
00:23:56,869 --> 00:23:59,036
        MY MOUTH IS DRY.        


331
00:24:00,740 --> 00:24:04,642
    <i> I'M CALM, BUT I'M SCARED.</i>  


332
00:24:07,313 --> 00:24:10,147
    I FEEL MY HEART             
    POUNDING IN MY EARS.        


333
00:24:12,385 --> 00:24:14,218
<i>[ Young Sydney ]</i>                
<i>IT'S TIME TO TELL THE TRUTH.</i>    


334
00:24:14,286 --> 00:24:18,288
                I DID.          
THIS IS YOUR LAST CHANCE.       


335
00:24:18,357 --> 00:24:20,457
    I DID TELL THE TRUTH.       


336
00:24:20,526 --> 00:24:24,027
    YOU'RE ABOUT TO DIE.        
    CLEAR YOUR CONSCIENCE.      


337
00:24:24,096 --> 00:24:27,098
IT IS CLEAR.                    
I'M AT PEACE.                   


338
00:24:29,234 --> 00:24:33,271
ROSENBERG WAS TELLING           
THE TRUTH, SYDNEY. HE DIDN'T    
GIVE THE SECRETS AWAY.          


339
00:24:35,442 --> 00:24:38,175
        - ARE YOU SURE?         
        - YES.                  


340
00:24:38,244 --> 00:24:40,478
        AREN'T YOU?             


341
00:24:42,449 --> 00:24:44,382
<i>[ Young Sydney ]</i>                
<i>YES.</i>                            


342
00:24:44,450 --> 00:24:47,118
<i>[ Young Jarod ]</i>                 
<i>BUT IF THEY KNEW</i>                
<i>HE WAS INNOCENT,</i>                


343
00:24:47,187 --> 00:24:49,119
WHY DID THEY EXECUTE HIM?       


344
00:24:49,188 --> 00:24:51,522
<i>[ Young Sydney ]</i>                
<i>WHAT DO YOU THINK?</i>              


345
00:24:53,393 --> 00:24:57,462
    BECAUSE SOMEONE             
    HAD TO BE GUILTY.           


346
00:25:07,474 --> 00:25:09,507
[ Cell Door Clattering ]        


347
00:25:30,363 --> 00:25:32,696
        TIGHTEN IT.             


348
00:25:32,765 --> 00:25:36,133
    I DON'T WANT THE PRISONER   
    TO GO INTO SPASM            
    AND BREAK THOSE STRAPS.     


349
00:25:57,023 --> 00:25:59,656
        INITIATE THE SEQUENCE.  


350
00:26:10,102 --> 00:26:13,503
        [ Breathing Heavily ]   


351
00:26:21,447 --> 00:26:25,382
    LARSON, DROP THE PELLETS.   


352
00:26:35,828 --> 00:26:37,928
                [ Beeps ]       


353
00:26:52,612 --> 00:26:55,579
WHY THE HESITATION?             
        MISTAKE                 
        IN COMMUNICATIONS, SIR. 


354
00:26:55,648 --> 00:26:57,581
                IT WON'T HAPPEN 
                AT SHOWTIME.    


355
00:26:57,650 --> 00:26:59,716
<i>[ Warden ]</i>                      
<i>YEAH, WELL,</i>                     
<i>SEE THAT IT DOESN'T.</i>            


356
00:26:59,785 --> 00:27:02,386
'CAUSE WE'RE GONNA HAVE         
A ROOMFUL OF PRESS BACK THERE   
FOR THE REAL EXECUTION,         


357
00:27:02,454 --> 00:27:05,189
AND I DON'T WANNA               
HAVE TO KILL CARL WILL TWICE.   


358
00:27:10,229 --> 00:27:12,563
    GET HIM OUT OF THERE.       
                    <i> [ Larson ]</i> 
                    <i> YES, SIR.</i>  


359
00:27:17,503 --> 00:27:19,437
                THANKS, BRADLEY.


360
00:27:38,858 --> 00:27:41,324
DO YOU KNOW WHAT'S WRONG        
WITH ME OR NOT?                 


361
00:27:41,393 --> 00:27:43,427
    I THINK YOU HAVE            
    AN ULCER.                   


362
00:27:43,496 --> 00:27:48,331
AND FROM THE WAY YOU WERE       
FOLDED UP WHEN I GOT HERE,      
IT'S A DOOZY.                   


363
00:27:49,935 --> 00:27:53,470
    - WHAT CAN BE DONE?         
    -<i> FOR NOW, I'M GOING</i>        
     <i> TO PRESCRIBE...</i>           


364
00:27:53,539 --> 00:27:56,606
        <i> A MILD ACID INHIBITOR.</i> 


365
00:27:58,044 --> 00:28:01,011
I'M NOT SURE                    
THAT IT WILL BE HELPFUL,        


366
00:28:01,080 --> 00:28:03,014
    GIVEN THE FACT              
    THAT SHE SMOKES...          


367
00:28:03,082 --> 00:28:07,351
        <i> AND HAS AN UNUSUALLY</i>   
        <i> STRESSFUL DEMEANOR.</i>    


368
00:28:07,420 --> 00:28:09,352
        YOU CAN SAY THAT AGAIN. 


369
00:28:09,421 --> 00:28:12,756
        <i> I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT IS</i>
        <i> YOU DO, MISS PARKER,</i>   


370
00:28:12,824 --> 00:28:16,160
BUT IT'S EATING YOU AWAY        
FROM THE INSIDE OUT.            


371
00:28:16,228 --> 00:28:18,795
    <i> YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE</i>       
    <i> TO CHANGE YOUR LIFESTYLE...</i>


372
00:28:18,864 --> 00:28:21,665
                    <i> OR ELSE.</i>   
    OR ELSE WHAT?               


373
00:28:21,734 --> 00:28:23,868
        YOU COULD DIE.          


374
00:28:23,936 --> 00:28:27,972
    <i> I SUGGEST THAT YOU LEARN</i>   
    <i> TO CONTROL YOUR EMOTIONS.</i>  


375
00:28:28,040 --> 00:28:32,509
LIKE YOUR FATHER HERE.          
HAVE A PLEASANT EVENING.        


376
00:28:32,578 --> 00:28:35,179
            <i> [ Sydney ]</i>         
            <i> THANK YOU, DOCTOR.</i> 
        <i> [ Broots ] THANKS, DOC.</i>


377
00:28:36,415 --> 00:28:38,348
        HE'S RIGHT, YOU KNOW.   


378
00:28:39,852 --> 00:28:44,120
        IF YOU DON'T KEEP       
        THOSE FEELINGS          
        ABOUT JAROD IN CHECK,   


379
00:28:44,189 --> 00:28:46,123
        IT COULD BE YOUR RUIN.  


380
00:28:47,626 --> 00:28:51,328
IT'S A LITTLE LATE              
TO BE WORRIED ABOUT MY RUIN.    


381
00:28:51,397 --> 00:28:53,364
        [ Clamoring ]           


382
00:28:53,432 --> 00:28:56,233
                    <i> MY FLOWERS!</i>


383
00:29:11,717 --> 00:29:13,884
                    BREAK IT UP!


384
00:29:15,488 --> 00:29:17,855
    - NO, BOSS!                 
    -<i> [ Warden ] CLANCY!</i>        


385
00:29:17,924 --> 00:29:20,390
    CLEAN UP THIS MESS.         


386
00:29:24,563 --> 00:29:26,764
        GET 'EM BACK            
        IN THEIR CAGES NOW.     


387
00:29:26,833 --> 00:29:32,736
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>ALL RIGHT, CLEAR THE YARD!</i>      
<i>MOVE IT!</i>                        


388
00:29:32,804 --> 00:29:36,039
    YOU EVER MAKE A MOVE        
    LIKE THAT ON ME AGAIN,      
    I'LL PUT YOU<i> IN</i> THIS PLOT.  


389
00:29:36,108 --> 00:29:38,509
        I JUST DIDN'T WANT      
        MY FLOWERS TRAMPLED.    


390
00:29:38,578 --> 00:29:41,378
        WELL, THAT WON'T BE     
        A PROBLEM NOW, WILL IT? 


391
00:29:52,124 --> 00:29:55,625
                YOU OKAY?       
SURE. FINE.                     


392
00:29:55,694 --> 00:29:57,627
                    YOU'RE SURE?


393
00:30:27,659 --> 00:30:29,760
WHERE'S MY WIFE?                


394
00:30:30,963 --> 00:30:34,832
SHE DIED THREE YEARS AGO.       
CANCER.                         


395
00:30:36,335 --> 00:30:39,569
                I'M SORRY.      
PRETTY PATHETIC, HUH?           


396
00:30:39,638 --> 00:30:42,072
                            NO. 


397
00:30:42,141 --> 00:30:45,676
            YOU LOCK A MAN AWAY 
            LONG ENOUGH,        


398
00:30:45,745 --> 00:30:47,711
                IT BENDS HIM,   


399
00:30:48,748 --> 00:30:50,681
                SOMETIMES       
                TILL HE BREAKS. 


400
00:30:54,220 --> 00:30:57,755
RITA AND ME                     
WERE MARRIED 43 YEARS.          


401
00:30:57,823 --> 00:30:59,757
YOU DIDN'T KNOW THAT,           
DID YOU?                        


402
00:30:59,825 --> 00:31:01,892
                NO, I DIDN'T.   


403
00:31:01,961 --> 00:31:06,996
I BROKE THE LAW,                
AND I'VE PAID EVERY DAY         
FOR THE LAST 27 YEARS.          


404
00:31:07,065 --> 00:31:09,700
BUT THERE'S CERTAIN THINGS      
THAT A MAN...                   


405
00:31:09,769 --> 00:31:13,136
CAN'T ALLOW                     
TO BE TAKEN FROM HIM.           


406
00:31:13,205 --> 00:31:18,675
HIS PRIDE,                      
 HIS DIGNITY.                   


407
00:31:18,744 --> 00:31:22,279
    I UNDERSTAND RULES.         


408
00:31:22,348 --> 00:31:27,217
BUT WHAT WARDEN MICHAELS        
DID TO ME WAS WRONG.            


409
00:31:27,286 --> 00:31:31,054
ALL I WANTED                    
WAS TO BE THERE WHEN...         


410
00:31:31,123 --> 00:31:35,192
MY RITA WAS LAID DOWN.          


411
00:31:35,261 --> 00:31:39,896
    I PUT HER THROUGH           
    A LOT OF PAIN.              


412
00:31:39,965 --> 00:31:43,167
AND I JUST WANTED TO BE ABLE    
TO PUT FLOWERS ON HER GRAVE...  


413
00:31:43,236 --> 00:31:48,372
AND FEEL HER IN MY HEART...     


414
00:31:48,441 --> 00:31:50,374
    ONE MORE TIME.              


415
00:31:50,443 --> 00:31:53,911
HE WOULDN'T GIVE ME             
A FURLOUGH.                     


416
00:31:53,979 --> 00:31:56,046
HELL, THEY--                    


417
00:31:56,114 --> 00:32:00,383
THEY LET CONS OUT               
FOR THAT KIND OF THING          
EVERY DAY.                      


418
00:32:00,452 --> 00:32:04,354
    ALL I WANTED TO DO          
    WAS SAY GOOD-BYE.           


419
00:32:06,125 --> 00:32:08,993
        IS THAT WHY YOU PLANTED 
        YOUR GARDEN?            


420
00:32:10,596 --> 00:32:12,529
        CRAZY, HUH?             


421
00:32:14,233 --> 00:32:16,867
I KEEP PRAYING MAYBE...         


422
00:32:16,936 --> 00:32:22,372
ONE DAY I'LL ACTUALLY           
GET THE CHANCE TO SHOW          
HOW MUCH I LOVED HER.           


423
00:32:22,441 --> 00:32:25,875
BUT MICHAELS--                  
HE'S SET ON MAKING...           


424
00:32:25,945 --> 00:32:29,212
A STATEMENT                     
WITH THIS PLACE.                


425
00:32:30,783 --> 00:32:34,351
    <i> I GUESS MAYBE</i>              
    <i> THEY WERE MY STATEMENT.</i>    


426
00:32:35,754 --> 00:32:40,291
    I JUST DIDN'T WANT THEM     
    TO THINK THEY BROKE ME.     


427
00:33:28,207 --> 00:33:31,108
[ Slinky Clanging ]             


428
00:33:32,844 --> 00:33:34,912
                HEY, BUDDY.     
                <i> [ Boy ]</i>        
                <i> HEY, WAIT UP!</i>  


429
00:33:34,980 --> 00:33:38,348
        I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND.  
        I BROUGHT YOUR KIDS     
        SOME TOYS.              


430
00:33:38,417 --> 00:33:40,350
HI, CUTIE.                      
GIVE THIS TO YOUR MOTHER.       


431
00:33:40,419 --> 00:33:42,419
TELL HER I'LL BE THERE          
IN A SECOND, OKAY?              


432
00:33:44,556 --> 00:33:47,090
            YOU HAVE            
            A BEAUTIFUL FAMILY. 


433
00:33:47,159 --> 00:33:50,060
            <i> YOU'RE A LUCKY MAN.</i>
    THANKS.                     


434
00:33:53,132 --> 00:33:55,465
SOMETHING ON YOUR MIND?         


435
00:33:55,534 --> 00:33:57,434
            CARL WILL.          


436
00:34:00,939 --> 00:34:04,641
                WHAT ABOUT HIM? 
WELL, I'M A LITTLE BIT          
EMBARRASSED TO ADMIT THIS,      


437
00:34:04,710 --> 00:34:08,412
BUT I'M NOT SURE                
I CAN HANDLE THIS EXECUTION.    


438
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:12,849
I KNOW IT'S WHAT WE DO,         
BUT I'VE NEVER SEEN             
A MAN DIE BEFORE.               


439
00:34:12,918 --> 00:34:16,052
I WAS HOPING                    
YOU COULD HELP ME.              


440
00:34:16,121 --> 00:34:19,723
            WELL, YOU'RE TALKING
            TO THE WRONG MAN.   
YEAH.                           


441
00:34:20,993 --> 00:34:23,560
I SAW YOUR FACE AS WE WERE      
DOING THE WALK-THROUGH.         


442
00:34:23,629 --> 00:34:28,365
IT'S PRETTY DIFFICULT           
FOR YOU TO IMAGINE CARL WILL    
STRAPPED TO THAT CHAIR,         


443
00:34:28,434 --> 00:34:32,736
GAS RISING UP,                  
CHOKING THE LIFE OUT OF HIM.    


444
00:34:34,272 --> 00:34:36,673
WHY IS THAT?                    


445
00:34:36,742 --> 00:34:39,409
            IT JUST IS, OKAY?   


446
00:34:40,846 --> 00:34:42,379
                            HMM.


447
00:34:46,084 --> 00:34:49,853
DID YOU EVER NOTICE             
THAT THESE THINGS               
ARE JUST LIKE GUILT?            


448
00:34:51,256 --> 00:34:54,591
YOU CAN MOVE IT                 
FROM ONE PLACE TO ANOTHER,      


449
00:34:54,660 --> 00:34:57,260
BUT IT ALWAYS COMES BACK.       


450
00:34:58,331 --> 00:35:00,230
                WHO ARE YOU?    


451
00:35:00,299 --> 00:35:03,500
SOMEONE WHO DOESN'T WANT        
TO SEE AN INNOCENT MAN DIE.     


452
00:35:03,569 --> 00:35:06,870
<i>SOMEONE WHO THINKS</i>              
<i>THAT JESSICA WILL DESERVES</i>      
<i>TO HAVE HER FATHER,</i>             


453
00:35:06,939 --> 00:35:09,773
JUST AS MUCH AS THOSE KIDS      
DESERVE TO HAVE THEIRS.         


454
00:35:17,283 --> 00:35:19,749
        I'VE BEEN WALKING       
        THE YARD FOR 20 YEARS.  


455
00:35:19,818 --> 00:35:22,419
                IT'S ALL I KNOW.


456
00:35:22,487 --> 00:35:25,289
        IT'S TOO LATE           
        TO START OVER, AND...   


457
00:35:25,357 --> 00:35:29,659
        I CAN'T AFFORD TO CROSS 
        A GUY LIKE CLANCY.      


458
00:35:29,728 --> 00:35:32,395
YOU'RE AFRAID FOR YOUR LIFE.    
            YEAH, WELL,         
            YOU SHOULD BE TOO.  


459
00:35:32,464 --> 00:35:36,867
            YOU KNOW HOW IT IS  
            ON THE INSIDE.      
            THINGS HAPPEN.      


460
00:35:36,936 --> 00:35:41,571
    AND I'M DAMN SURE NOT GONNA 
    END UP LIKE ANTHONY LEWIS   
    AND THE OTHERS.             


461
00:35:41,640 --> 00:35:45,008
LEWIS WAS TRANSFERRED IN        
FROM JOLIET.                    


462
00:35:45,076 --> 00:35:47,444
JUST LIKE ALL THE OTHER MEN     
WHO DIED HERE.                  


463
00:35:47,513 --> 00:35:50,079
I PULLED THE INMATES' FILES,    
AND I TRACKED THEM.             


464
00:35:50,148 --> 00:35:52,081
IT'S REALLY INTERESTING.        


465
00:35:52,151 --> 00:35:55,985
EACH ONE OF THEM                
BELONGED TO THE SAME            
CHICAGO CRIME FAMILY.           


466
00:35:56,054 --> 00:36:00,290
MY GUESS WOULD BE               
THAT SOMEBODY PAID              
TO HAVE THEM SILENCED.          


467
00:36:00,359 --> 00:36:02,793
IS THAT THE WAY                 
THE OPERATION WORKED?           


468
00:36:04,429 --> 00:36:06,796
            YEAH. CLANCY'S      
            BROTHER-IN-LAW...   


469
00:36:06,866 --> 00:36:10,834
            IS A PENCIL PUSHER  
            AT JOLIET.          


470
00:36:10,903 --> 00:36:12,836
            HE MADE A DEAL      
            WITH A RIVAL FAMILY.


471
00:36:12,905 --> 00:36:14,905
        THEY TRANSFERRED TARGETS
        INTO OAKFIELD.          


472
00:36:14,974 --> 00:36:17,941
        CLANCY DOES THE JOB.    
        THEY SPLIT THE MONEY.   


473
00:36:18,010 --> 00:36:20,476
ARE YOU A PART OF IT?           


474
00:36:20,545 --> 00:36:22,546
            NO, I WASN'T.       


475
00:36:22,614 --> 00:36:25,549
I DIDN'T FIND OUT UNTIL         
AFTER ANTHONY LEWIS WAS KILLED. 


476
00:36:25,617 --> 00:36:27,951
            AND BY THEN,        
            I WAS IN TOO DEEP   
            TO SAY ANYTHING.    


477
00:36:28,020 --> 00:36:30,153
WHAT ABOUT CARL WILL?           


478
00:36:32,725 --> 00:36:36,125
CLANCY WAS FINISHING UP         
ON LEWIS, AND WILL WALKED IN.   


479
00:36:36,195 --> 00:36:38,127
    I WAS SUPPOSED TO MAKE SURE 
    THE AREA WAS CLEAR.         


480
00:36:38,197 --> 00:36:42,699
            HELL, I THOUGHT     
            HE WAS JUST HITTING 
            THE GUY UP FOR CASH.


481
00:36:42,767 --> 00:36:45,334
IS THAT WHEN                    
YOU KNOCKED HIM OUT?            
        YEAH, WELL, I HAD TO.   


482
00:36:45,403 --> 00:36:48,671
        CLANCY WOULD HAVE KILLED
        THE GUY RIGHT THERE.    


483
00:36:48,740 --> 00:36:52,008
            CLANCY PLANTED      
            THE SHIV ON HIM.    


484
00:36:53,545 --> 00:36:56,880
                BY THE TIME     
                WILL CAME TO,   


485
00:36:56,949 --> 00:36:59,015
                    IT WAS OVER.


486
00:37:02,087 --> 00:37:04,922
AND NOW                         
HE'S GOING TO DIE...            


487
00:37:04,990 --> 00:37:07,290
FOR SOMETHING                   
HE DIDN'T DO.                   


488
00:37:13,798 --> 00:37:17,066
<i>[ Broots ]</i>                      
<i>THERE'S DEFINITELY SOMETHING</i>    
<i>WRONG WITH THIS GAME.</i>           


489
00:37:17,135 --> 00:37:19,469
    MAYBE NOT ALL THE PIECES    
    ARE THERE.                  


490
00:37:19,538 --> 00:37:22,172
        THEY'RE NOT,            
        THEY'RE NOT,            
        BUT IT'S MORE THAN THAT.


491
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:26,209
<i>I HAVE A FEELING</i>                
<i>WE'RE NOT SEEING SOMETHING</i>      
<i>IMPORTANT WITH THIS WHOLE THING.</i>


492
00:37:26,278 --> 00:37:28,211
                [ Pills Rattle ]


493
00:37:30,148 --> 00:37:33,917
            SPEAK FOR YOURSELF. 
            GOT US A STETSON.   


494
00:37:36,455 --> 00:37:39,723
                <i> [ Gun Cocks ]</i>  
            WELL, I HEAR THAT.  


495
00:37:39,792 --> 00:37:41,691
    TWITCH AND YOUR NEXT STOP   
    IS BOOT HILL.               


496
00:37:41,760 --> 00:37:45,695
HEY, RELAX, LITTLE LADY.        
I'M JUST THE PONY EXPRESS.      


497
00:37:45,764 --> 00:37:49,499
    PUT THE PHONE DOWN          
    AND TURN AROUND... SLOWLY.  


498
00:37:55,140 --> 00:37:58,608
THAT'S AN AWFULLY BIG GUN       
FOR SUCH A PRETTY LITTLE LADY.  


499
00:37:58,676 --> 00:38:02,546
        SAVE IT FOR THE HOEDOWN.
        WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?


500
00:38:02,614 --> 00:38:05,048
WELL, I TOLD YOU.               
I WAS PAID TO MAKE A DELIVERY.  


501
00:38:05,117 --> 00:38:07,718
        YES. WHAT KIND          
        OF DELIVERY?            


502
00:38:08,854 --> 00:38:11,354
    HEY, I'M UNARMED.           
    I SWEAR.                    


503
00:38:11,422 --> 00:38:14,257
                LEFT HAND ONLY. 


504
00:38:27,506 --> 00:38:29,539
            I KNEW THERE WAS    
            SOMETHING MISSING.  


505
00:38:29,607 --> 00:38:31,641
                WHAT ARE YOU    
                TALKING ABOUT?  


506
00:38:32,878 --> 00:38:37,647
<i>THE GAME. CHANCE.</i>               
<i>GET OUT OF JAIL FREE.</i>           


507
00:38:37,716 --> 00:38:40,650
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>WHAT DO YOU THINK</i>               
<i>IT MEANS, MISS PARKER?</i>          


508
00:38:44,356 --> 00:38:46,289
                DAMN IT.        


509
00:38:46,358 --> 00:38:48,591
        I NEED TO SEE           
        YOUR REGISTRATION BOOK. 


510
00:38:48,660 --> 00:38:50,660
                    <i> [ Clerk ]</i>  
                    <i> OKAY.</i>      


511
00:38:50,729 --> 00:38:53,096
                [ Muttering ]   


512
00:38:53,165 --> 00:38:55,598
            <i> [ Pages Turning ]</i>  


513
00:38:55,667 --> 00:39:00,136
            "JAROD SHORT.       
             JAROD ST. JAMES.   
             JAROD VENTNOR.     


514
00:39:00,205 --> 00:39:04,607
        JAROD CHANCE.           
        MARVIN GARDENS.         
        ROOM 5." THE ROOM--     


515
00:39:04,676 --> 00:39:07,944
            THE ROOM            
            RIGHT NEXT TO OURS. 


516
00:39:24,129 --> 00:39:27,731
        <i> [ Sydney ]</i>             
        <i> "GO DIRECTLY TO JAIL.</i>  
         <i> DO NOT PASS GO.</i>       


517
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:30,800
        <i> DO NOT COLLECT $200."</i>  


518
00:39:33,172 --> 00:39:36,373
    I AM SICK OF BEING A TOKEN  
    ON HIS GAME BOARD.          


519
00:39:38,243 --> 00:39:40,176
                MISS PARKER.    


520
00:39:49,054 --> 00:39:50,987
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>GO DIRECTLY TO JAIL.</i>            


521
00:39:52,090 --> 00:39:54,624
        DAMN YOU, JAROD.        


522
00:39:54,692 --> 00:39:59,062
        [ Chanting ]            
        FREE CARL WILL.         
        FREE CARL WILL.         


523
00:40:00,132 --> 00:40:04,001
                    HEY, CLANCY.


524
00:40:04,069 --> 00:40:06,302
        THE WARDEN JUST CALLED. 


525
00:40:06,371 --> 00:40:08,304
        HE WANTS YOU            
        TO MAKE ANOTHER CHECK   
        OF THE GAS CHAMBER.     


526
00:40:08,373 --> 00:40:10,907
        MAKE SURE               
        THERE'S NO MALFUNCTIONS.
IT'S FINE.                      


527
00:40:10,976 --> 00:40:12,976
I LOADED THE CYANIDE MYSELF     
NOT AN HOUR AGO.                


528
00:40:13,045 --> 00:40:15,245
                HEY, DON'T SHOOT
                THE MESSENGER.  


529
00:40:15,313 --> 00:40:17,247
        GUESS THERE'S SOME KIND 
        OF ELECTRICAL PROBLEM.  


530
00:40:17,316 --> 00:40:19,248
HAVE LARSON CHECK IT.           


531
00:40:19,318 --> 00:40:21,684
        <i> HIS WIFE JUST CALLED.</i>  
        <i> HE'S SICK.</i>             


532
00:40:21,753 --> 00:40:26,256
    MY BUTT.                    
    HE'S YELLOW.                
    YOU CHECK IT.               


533
00:40:26,324 --> 00:40:28,424
                I CAN'T.        
                I'M THE NEW GUY.


534
00:40:28,493 --> 00:40:31,127
        <i> I HAVE TO BRING WILL</i>   
        <i> HIS LAST SUPPER.</i>       


535
00:40:31,196 --> 00:40:33,330
ALL RIGHT, DAMN IT.             


536
00:40:33,398 --> 00:40:35,331
YOU NEED SOMETHING              
DONE RIGHT--                    


537
00:40:35,401 --> 00:40:37,534
                DO IT YOURSELF. 


538
00:40:56,055 --> 00:40:59,790
    WELL, GOOD THING            
    WE'RE NOT FRYING THIS GUY.  


539
00:41:00,793 --> 00:41:02,793
<i>[ Door Opens ]</i>                  


540
00:41:02,861 --> 00:41:07,130
                WARDEN MICHAELS?
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>                 


541
00:41:22,715 --> 00:41:25,748
<i>[ Clancy ]</i>                      
<i>HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?</i>      
<i>WHO SHUT THE DOOR?</i>              


542
00:41:25,817 --> 00:41:27,950
                WHO'S THERE?    


543
00:41:29,021 --> 00:41:31,254
                SCARY, ISN'T IT?


544
00:41:31,323 --> 00:41:34,724
        BEING LOCKED UP         
        LIKE A WILD ANIMAL...   


545
00:41:34,793 --> 00:41:37,393
                WAITING TO DIE. 


546
00:41:37,462 --> 00:41:39,762
FUNNY, BRADLEY.                 
NOW LET ME OUT.                 


547
00:41:39,831 --> 00:41:41,865
                    MM.         


548
00:41:43,702 --> 00:41:45,768
                I DON'T THINK   
                I'LL DO THAT.   


549
00:41:47,172 --> 00:41:49,505
WHAT THE HELL                   
DO YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING?      


550
00:41:49,574 --> 00:41:51,508
            SAME THING          
            YOU'VE BEEN DOING.  


551
00:41:53,745 --> 00:41:56,747
        [ Clancy On Intercom ]  
        I DON'T KNOW WHAT       
        YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.   


552
00:41:56,815 --> 00:41:59,783
        [ Jarod On Intercom ]   
        OH, COME ON, CLANCY.    


553
00:41:59,852 --> 00:42:02,819
            I KNOW YOU KILLED   
            ANTHONY LEWIS.      


554
00:42:02,888 --> 00:42:05,755
    YOU SET UP CARL WILL        
    TO TAKE THE FALL FOR IT.    


555
00:42:08,326 --> 00:42:11,161
    YOU WERE GOING TO LET       
    AN INNOCENT MAN DIE...      


556
00:42:11,229 --> 00:42:14,530
<i>FOR SOMETHING YOU DID.</i>          
<i>[ Clucking Tongue ]</i>             


557
00:42:16,267 --> 00:42:18,201
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?           


558
00:42:18,270 --> 00:42:21,671
                I'M YOU--       
                JUDGE,          


559
00:42:23,575 --> 00:42:26,342
                        <i> JURY--</i> 
            <i> [ Switch Clicks ]</i>  


560
00:42:26,411 --> 00:42:29,212
                AND EXECUTIONER.
            <i> [ Switch Clicks ]</i>  


561
00:42:33,919 --> 00:42:36,353
                HOW MANY MEN?   


562
00:42:36,421 --> 00:42:38,855
        <i> HOW MANY MEN</i>           
        <i> DID YOU KILL, CLANCY?</i>  


563
00:42:39,925 --> 00:42:42,892
                FIVE? SIX?      


564
00:42:42,961 --> 00:42:45,127
    THEY WERE ANIMALS.          


565
00:42:45,196 --> 00:42:47,930
<i>I DID THE PUBLIC A FAVOR.</i>       


566
00:42:47,999 --> 00:42:50,333
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>AND YOU ALMOST</i>                  
<i>GOT AWAY WITH IT.</i>               


567
00:42:50,402 --> 00:42:54,336
<i>EXCEPT CARL WILL</i>                
<i>WAS AT THE WRONG PLACE</i>          
<i>AT THE WRONG TIME.</i>              


568
00:42:54,405 --> 00:42:56,339
<i>[ Clancy ]</i>                      
<i>NAME YOUR PRICE.</i>                


569
00:42:56,407 --> 00:42:58,808
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>MY PRICE?</i>                       


570
00:42:58,877 --> 00:43:00,843
<i>MONEY.</i>                          


571
00:43:00,912 --> 00:43:05,381
    <i> HOW MUCH IS A HUMAN LIFE</i>   
    <i> WORTH ANYWAY?</i>              


572
00:43:05,450 --> 00:43:07,883
        <i> HOW MUCH DID YOU MAKE?</i> 


573
00:43:07,953 --> 00:43:11,488
                <i> 5,000?</i>         
                <i> 10,000 A HEAD?</i> 


574
00:43:12,824 --> 00:43:17,894
        NAH, I THINK            
        IT'S TIME FOR JUSTICE   
        TO WIN THIS ONE.        


575
00:43:20,198 --> 00:43:22,332
            <i> I'D ASK IF YOU HAD</i> 
            <i> A LAST REQUEST,</i>    


576
00:43:22,400 --> 00:43:24,667
            BUT THE TRUTH IS,   


577
00:43:26,838 --> 00:43:30,340
                YOU DON'T REALLY
                DESERVE IT.     


578
00:43:32,244 --> 00:43:34,710
            IT'S SHOWTIME.      


579
00:43:35,580 --> 00:43:38,214
            [ Beeps ]           


580
00:43:42,087 --> 00:43:45,521
        - NO!                   
        - [ Sizzles ]           


581
00:43:45,590 --> 00:43:49,392
<i>[ Clancy Yelling, Indistinct ]</i>  


582
00:43:50,762 --> 00:43:52,695
        DON'T YOU THINK         
        NOT TELLING THAT MAN... 


583
00:43:52,764 --> 00:43:57,767
        THOSE CYANIDE CAPSULES  
        WERE FAKE IS CRUEL      
        AND UNUSUAL PUNISHMENT? 


584
00:43:57,835 --> 00:44:00,870
<i>[ Clancy ]</i>                      
<i>BRADLEY! AAH!</i>                   
        NAH.                    


585
00:44:00,938 --> 00:44:03,939
<i>[ Clancy Screaming ]</i>            


586
00:44:06,044 --> 00:44:08,712
        I, UH, WOULD BE HAPPY   
        TO ANSWER ANY QUESTIONS 
        YOU HAVE,               


587
00:44:08,780 --> 00:44:13,182
    BUT RIGHT NOW,              
    I'D LIKE TO HUG MY DAD...   


588
00:44:13,251 --> 00:44:15,184
            AND TELL HIM        
            HOW MUCH I LOVE HIM.


589
00:44:15,253 --> 00:44:17,186
        [ Miss Parker ]         
        GET OUT OF MY WAY.      


590
00:44:17,255 --> 00:44:20,156
    [ Reporters Clamoring ]     


591
00:44:20,225 --> 00:44:23,159
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>HEY, YOU, OPEN UP.</i>              
<i>WE'RE EXPECTED.</i>                 


592
00:44:23,228 --> 00:44:25,661
<i>[ Buzzer Buzzes ]</i>               


593
00:44:35,274 --> 00:44:37,340
    NO CIVILIZED PERSON         
    COULD SIT HERE              
    IN FRONT OF YOU PEOPLE...   


594
00:44:37,408 --> 00:44:40,543
AND TELL YOU THAT               
HE ENJOYS GIVING THE ORDER...   


595
00:44:40,612 --> 00:44:44,347
<i>TO HAVE CYANIDE PELLETS...</i>      


596
00:44:44,416 --> 00:44:49,085
<i>DROPPED INTO ACID</i>               
<i>TO KILL SOMEONE.</i>                


597
00:44:49,154 --> 00:44:53,456
<i>BUT WE DO THAT TO DETER PEOPLE</i>  
<i>FROM COMMITTING CRIMES.</i>         


598
00:44:53,524 --> 00:44:58,127
<i>UNFORTUNATELY, THERE ARE EVENTS</i> 
<i>THAT WOULD PROVE WE HAVE</i>        
<i>CORRUPTION ON OUR STAFF.</i>        


599
00:45:03,535 --> 00:45:07,069
AND INSPIRED BY THESE EVENTS,   
CHANGES WILL BE MADE HERE...    


600
00:45:07,138 --> 00:45:09,472
        THAT HOPEFULLY BENEFIT  
        ALL THE INMATES.        


601
00:45:10,709 --> 00:45:13,743
            MY RESIGNATION      
            WILL BECOME FINAL   
            IN 24 HOURS,        


602
00:45:13,812 --> 00:45:16,546
    AFTER MY LAST OFFICIAL ACT  
    AS WARDEN.                  


603
00:45:52,450 --> 00:45:57,186
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>SO, WE UNDERSTAND</i>               
<i>YOU LIKE TO PLAY GAMES, MR.--</i>   


604
00:45:57,255 --> 00:46:00,923
    PARKER. YES.                
    AND I'VE INVENTED ONE.      


605
00:46:00,992 --> 00:46:04,660
    I CALL IT                   
    GET OUT OF JAIL FREE.       


606
00:46:36,528 --> 00:46:37,527
            [ Mews ]            


